\\title{AntClassify: An \\proglang{R} Package for Standardized Analysis of Ant Communities, Functional Guilds, Endemism, and Rarity}
\\Plainauthor{D. C. O. Gonçalves, N. S. da Silva, R. P. Santos, L. P. do Prado, M. S. C. C. Morini}
\\Plaintitle{AntClassify: An R Package for Standardized Analysis of Ant Communities}
\\Shorttitle{AntClassify}
\\Abstract{
The rapid pace of urbanization exerts significant pressure on ecosystems, leading to habitat fragmentation, biodiversity loss, and altered ecological functions. In this context, monitoring the health of urban ecosystems is essential to understand the effects of anthropogenic transformations and to support conservation and environmental management strategies. The growing availability of ecological and environmental data demands computational tools that integrate, standardize, and analyze such information in a reproducible and accessible manner. \\pkg{AntClassify} is an \\proglang{R} package designed to address this need by providing a comprehensive framework for ant community analysis. It automates the classification of ant species into functional guilds based on established literature as well as a novel classification derived from urban ant communities. The package also identifies exotic species recorded in Brazil, flags endemic species of the Atlantic Forest, and classifies rarity according to geographic distribution and local abundance. By standardizing and automating these ecological classifications, \\pkg{AntClassify} streamlines data analysis and contributes to studies in biodiversity, community ecology, and conservation. The package is freely available on CRAN under an open-source license.
}
\\Keywords{ant ecology, functional guilds, exotic species, endemism, rarity, \\proglang{R}}
\\Plainkeywords{ant ecology, functional guilds, exotic species, endemism, rarity, R}
